'''Mike Louis Penders''' (born 31 July 2005) is a Belgian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{English football updater|Chelsea}} club [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] and the [[Belgium national football team|Belgium national team]].

==Club career==
===Genk===
Penders is a youth product of Boorsem Sport and Bregel Sport, before moving to the academy of [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]] in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-08-26 |title=Mike Penders verlengt contract tot 2028 |url=https://www.krcgenk.be/nl/nieuws/5246/mike-penders-verlengt-contract-tot-2028 |access-date=2025-06-05 |website=KRC Genk |language=nl-BE}}</ref>

On 30 April 2021, he signed his first contract with Genk.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-04-30 |title=KRC Genk legt drie jonge talenten vast tot 2024 |url=https://www.hbvl.be/sport/voetbal/krc-genk-legt-drie-jonge-talenten-vast-tot-2024/29014328.html |access-date=2025-06-05 |website=HBVL |language=nl-BE}}</ref> On 25 May 2022, he extended his contract until 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-05-25 |title=KRC Genk verlengt contract van jonge doelman Mike Penders (16) |url=https://www.hbvl.be/sport/voetbal/krc-genk-verlengt-contract-van-jonge-doelman-mike-penders-16/29839200.html |access-date=2025-06-05 |website=HBVL |language=nl-BE}}</ref>

In the [[2022–23 Challenger Pro League|2022–23 season]], he was promoted to their reserve team [[Jong Genk]].<ref name="auto" /> He made his debut in a 4–1 victory against [[Lierse S.K. (2018)|Lierse]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-08-14 |title=Met lef én een killer instinct: Jong Genk wint eerste profmatch met 4-1 van Lierse Kempenzonen |url=https://www.hbvl.be/sport/voetbal/met-lef-en-een-killer-instinct-jong-genk-wint-eerste-profmatch-met-4-1-van-lierse-kempenzonen/29959958.html |access-date=2025-06-05 |website=HBVL |language=nl-BE}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web |date=2024-08-27 |title=Official: Mike Penders makes top transfer to Chelsea FC |url=https://www.krcgenk.be/en/news/5633/official-mike-penders-makes-top-transfer-to-chelsea-fc |access-date=2025-06-05}}</ref>

On 23 August 2023, he again extended his contract until 2028.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hbvl.be/cnt/dmf20230827_95676885|title=KRC Genk verlengt contract van doelman Mike Penders tot 2028 (Jupiler Pro League) &#124; Het Belang van Limburg |date=27 August 2023 }}</ref> He was made captain of Jong Genk in the [[2023–24 Challenger Pro League|2023–24 season]]<ref name=":0" />

Following the departure of [[Maarten Vandevoordt]] and injury to [[Hendrik Van Crombrugge]], Penders made his senior debut with the Genk first team in a 0–0 [[Belgian Pro League]] tie with [[Standard Liège]] on 28 July 2024.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-07-26 |title=Penders (18) onder de lat bij Genk: ''Courtois is hier eveneens jong begonnen'' |url=https://www.voetbalprimeur.be/nieuws/1215433/keeper-mike-penders-18-verdedigt-doel-krc-genk-tegen-standard.html |access-date=2025-06-05 |website=VoetbalPrimeur.be |language=nl-BE}}</ref> At 18 years and 363 days, he was the third youngest goalkeeper to debut in the history of the league.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Geukens |first=Marnik |date=2024-07-29 |title=Chelsea zet zijn zinnen op 18-jarige Belgische doelman Mike Penders (KRC Genk) |url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20240729_95997452 |access-date=2025-06-05 |website=Het Nieuwsblad |language=nl-BE}}</ref>

In January 2025, Genk coach [[Thorsten Fink]] announced that Penders would be the team's starting goalkeeper for the remainder of the [[2024–25 Belgian Pro League|2024–25 season]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hbvl.be/sport/voetbal/fink-hakt-knoop-door-doelman-mike-penders-krijgt-ook-in-competitie-de-voorkeur-op-van-crombrugge/34940837.html|title=Fink hakt knoop door: doelman Mike Penders krijgt ook in competitie de voorkeur op Van Crombrugge|language=nl-BE|date=17 January 2025|access-date=16 May 2026|website=HBVL}}</ref> He ended the season having played 21 league matches, including all ten matches in the Championship play-offs.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.espn.com.au/football/player/stats/_/id/332343/team/938|title=Mike Penders Career Stats - Belgian Pro League|access-date=16 May 2026|website=ESPN}}</ref>

===Chelsea===
On 27 August 2024, it was announced that Penders would join [[Premier League]] club [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] in the summer of 2025.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-07-27 |title=Mike Penders to join Chelsea |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/penders-to-join-chelsea |access-date=2025-06-05 |website=Chelsea F.C. |language=en}}</ref>

In June 2025, Penders was named in Chelsea's squad for the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup]] in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/sports/2025/6/13/fifa-club-world-cup-2025-full-squad-list-of-all-teams-and-players|title=FIFA Club World Cup 2025: Full squad list of all teams and players|date=13 June 2025|access-date=16 May 2026|website=Al Jazeera}}</ref> He was an unused substitute in [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup final|the final]] on 13 July 2025.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/735958/paris-saint-germain-chelsea|title=Chelsea 3-0 PSG|date=13 June 2025|access-date=16 May 2026|website=ESPN}}</ref>

====Loan to Strasbourg====
On 28 July 2025, Penders joined [[Ligue 1]] club [[RC Strasbourg Alsace|Strasbourg]] on a season-long loan deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/mike-penders-joins-strasbourg-on-loan|title=Mike Penders joins Strasbourg on loan|website=www.chelseafc.com|date=28 July 2025|accessdate=28 July 2025}}</ref>

He made his debut for Strasbourg in their opening [[2025–26 Ligue 1|Ligue 1]] fixture on 17 August, keeping a clean sheet against [[FC Metz|Metz]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/ligue-1/articles/rc-strasbourg-kicks-off-ligue-1-with-a-win-against-fc-metz-thanks-to-a-stunning-goal-from-panichelli-2025-08-17|title=RC Strasbourg Kicks Off Ligue 1 With a Win Against FC Metz Thanks to a Stunning Goal From Joaquín Panichelli|date=17 August 2025|access-date=16 May 2026|website=beIN Sports}}</ref> He was an ever present in Strasbourg's runs to the semi-finals of both the [[2025–26 Coupe de France|Coupe de France]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/resultats-matchs/match-nice-strasbourg-1340-1146/|title=Strasbourg 0-2 Nice|date=22 April 2026|access-date=16 May 2026|website=Ouest France}}</ref> and [[2025–26 UEFA Conference League|UEFA Conference League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rtbf.be/article/conference-league-strasbourg-a-un-but-a-remonter-pour-esperer-eliminer-le-rayo-vallecano-direct-video-21h-11720105|title=Mike Penders n’a pas suffi : Strasbourg éliminé aux portes de la finale de Conference League par le Rayo Vallecano|date=7 May 2026|access-date=16 May 2026|language=French|website=RTBF}}</ref>

==International career==
Penders is a youth international for Belgium, having represented the nation at under-17, under-18, under-19 and under-21 level.

In 2023, he was called up to the [[Belgium national under-19 football team|Belgium U19]]s where he acted as captain during the [[2024 UEFA European Under-19 Championship qualification]] campaign.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hbvl.be/cnt/dmf20231121_95867484|title=Mike Penders en Josue Kongolo (KRC Genk) naar eliteronde EK 2024 &#124; Het Belang van Limburg |date=21 November 2023 }}</ref>

In 2025, Penders played four matches during [[2027 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification|qualification]] for the [[2027 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/teams/players/250160775--mike-penders/|title=Mike Penders|access-date=16 May 2026|website=UEFA}}</ref>

In August 2025, he received his first call up to the senior [[Belgium national football team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sport/voetbal/penders-seys-en-vanhoutte-zijn-er-voor-het-eerst-bij-terwijl-batshuayi-zijn-rentree-viert-bij-de-rode-duivels-dit-is-de-25-koppige-selectie-van-rudi-garcia/86890871.html|title=Penders, Seys en Vanhoutte zijn er voor het eerst bij, terwijl Batshuayi zijn rentree viert bij de Rode Duivels: dit is de 25-koppige selectie van Rudi Garcia|date=29 August 2025|access-date=16 May 2026|language=Dutch|website=Nieuwsblad}}</ref> On 18 November, he was an unused substitute in a 7–0 win over [[Liechtenstein national football team|Liechtenstein]] in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification|2026 FIFA World Cup qualifier]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/match/2025/nov/18/belgium-v-liechtenstein|title=Belgium 7-0 Liechtenstein|date=18 November 2025|access-date=16 May 2026|website=The Guardian}}</ref>

On 15 May 2026, he was named in Belgium's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/belgium-squad-garcia-lukaku-named|title=https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/belgium-squad-garcia-lukaku-named|date=15 May 2026|access-date=16 May 2026|website=FIFA}}</ref>

